---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Contact | The Princeton Journal"
  url="https://theprincetonjournal.com/contact"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-10">

    <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">
      Contact
    </p>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
      Contact The Princeton Journal
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-800">

      <p>
        For questions, corrections, tips, documents, or general inquiries, use the form below or email us directly at <strong>theprincetonjournal@gmail.com</strong>.
      </p>

      <p>
        For concerns about public registry data shown on this site, including correction requests, removal concerns, or
        displayed photo issues, include the SID, the listed name, and a short description of the issue so we can
        review it efficiently.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Princeton Journal can review how a public registry record appears on this site, but the underlying official
        registry record is controlled by Texas DPS and the registering agency. If the issue concerns the source record
        itself, users should also contact the official registry authority.
      </p>

      <form
        name="contact"
        method="POST"
        action="/thank-you"
        data-netlify="true"
        class="mt-8 space-y-6 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 p-6 shadow-sm"
      >

        <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="contact" />

        <div>
          <label class="mb-2 block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
            Your Email
          </label>
          <input
            type="email"
            name="email"
            required
            placeholder="you@example.com"
            class="w-full rounded-xl border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-base outline-none focus:border-black"
          />
        </div>

<div>
  <label class="mb-2 block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
    Subject
  </label>
  <select
    name="subject"
    required
    class="w-full rounded-xl border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-base outline-none focus:border-black bg-white"
  >
    <option value="">Select a subject</option>
    <option value="News Tip">News Tip</option>
    <option value="Correction Request">Correction Request</option>
    <option value="Registry Correction / Concern">Registry Correction / Concern</option>
    <option value="Clarification Request">Clarification Request</option>
    <option value="Document Submission">Document Submission</option>
    <option value="Public Records / FOIA">Public Records / FOIA</option>
    <option value="Story Idea">Story Idea</option>
    <option value="Interview / Comment Request">Interview / Comment Request</option>
    <option value="Partnership / Collaboration">Partnership / Collaboration</option>
    <option value="Advertising / Sponsorship">Advertising / Sponsorship</option>
    <option value="Technical Issue">Technical Issue</option>
    <option value="General Inquiry">General Inquiry</option>
    <option value="Other">Other</option>
  </select>
</div>

        <div>
          <label class="mb-2 block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
            Message
          </label>
          <textarea
            name="message"
            rows="8"
            required
            placeholder="Write your message here..."
            class="w-full rounded-xl border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-base outline-none focus:border-black"
          ></textarea>
        </div>

        <button
          type="submit"
          class="rounded-xl border border-black px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium transition hover:bg-black hover:text-white"
        >
          Submit
        </button>

      </form>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Tips and Documents
      </h2>

      <p>
        If you have records, documents, or information that may be relevant to the public, you may send them to the email above.
      </p>

      <p>
        Submission of information does not guarantee publication. All materials are reviewed for relevance, accuracy, and verification.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Corrections and Clarifications
      </h2>

      <p>
        If you believe an article contains an error or requires clarification, please contact us with the relevant details.
      </p>

      <p>
        If your concern involves public registry data, a displayed registry photo, or a removal concern about how a
        record appears on this site, please include the SID, the person’s name as shown on the page, and the specific
        issue.
      </p>

      <p>
        We can review presentation issues on this site, but we do not control the official registry entry maintained by
        Texas DPS or the registering agency.
      </p>

      <p>
        Corrections and clarifications are posted at the end of the relevant article with a timestamp and a note describing what changed.
      </p>

      <hr class="border-gray-200" />

      <p class="text-base text-gray-600">
        We appreciate readers who help strengthen local reporting by sharing information and engaging with the community responsibly.
      </p>

    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>
